5. That the Elector should maintain six thousand Men in _Italy_ at his own
expence, in case the Emperor should be obligaEuro(TM)d to go to War for the
_Spanish_ Succession.

6. That those Troops should remain there as long as the War continuaEuro(TM)d.

Thus, Madame, after tedious delays the Court of _Vienna_ consented at last
to the Success of this great Event, which after all owaEuro(TM)d its cause to the
