Coronation. This Ceremony cost him immense Sums of Money, and convincaEuro(TM)d
Foreigners who came thither from a curiosity to see it, that our Court was
inferior to few others for Magnificence.

ThoaEuro(TM) one would think the preparations for such a solemn Festival must take
up a tedious deal of time, yet the KingaEuro(TM)s Impatience hurryaEuro(TM)d them so fast
that every thing was ready by the eighteenth of _January_, about a
