took the Scepter and Globe from the hands of the Lords who carried them,
and the King raising her up she followaEuro(TM)d him into his Apartment, where she
also receivaEuro(TM)d the Homage of the Prince Royal and the Margraves, in the
same manner as they had performaEuro(TM)d them to the King.

Their Majesties went afterwards to Church with all the Pomp and
Magnificence, (I dare to say it) of the ancient Kings of _Asia_. The King
walkaEuro(TM)d under a Canopy of Silver-Brocade embroideraEuro(TM)d with Gold borne by ten
_Prussian_ Lords of the first Quality, and at some distance came the Queen
