very bloody one. The famous Battle of _Malplaquet_ was one of those
Victories which procured us Laurels coveraEuro(TM)d with Funeral Scutcheons, and
two more such Victories would have ruinaEuro(TM)d the Infantry of the Allies. The
Prince Royal was Witness of the Bravery of our Troops, which distinguishaEuro(TM)d
themselves in this Campaign, wherein they had been great Sufferers. The
Enemy on their part besides the Battle lost also _Mons_ and _Tournay_.

I could have wishaEuro(TM)d to have made this Campaign, but when I askaEuro(TM)d the
KingaEuro(TM)s Leave to go, his Majesty refusaEuro(TM)d me, saying, that he designaEuro(TM)d me
