who pacifyaEuro(TM)d me a little by giving me to understand, that if I did not
abate of my Fire I had nothing to do but to renounce all Advancement in
the Service of my King, a Service always preferable to any Fortunes that
can be made at the Court of any Foreign Prince. He promisaEuro(TM)d to set me
right in the KingaEuro(TM)s Opinion, and he kept his Word; for two or three Days
