the Square but the Windows and Roofs of the Houses were coveraEuro(TM)d with them.

From this Window his Majesty saw the Officers of the Empire perform their
Functions. The Count _de Papenheim_ the Elector of _Saxony_aEuro(TM)s Vicar, as
Grand Marshal of the Empire, was the first that began the Ceremony. He was
