The Elector-Palatine appearaEuro(TM)d next, encompassaEuro(TM)d with his Guards, and
preceded by his Courtiers. He went on horseback to a Kitchen built for the
purpose in the great Square, where he found a whole Ox roasting on a Spit,
of which he cut off a Slice, and putting it into a Gold Dish he carryaEuro(TM)d it
to the EmperoraEuro(TM)s Table.

The Count _de Zinzendorf_, Vicar to the Elector of _Hanover_ as Treasurer
of the Empire, came next. He was on horseback attended by the EmperoraEuro(TM)s
Guards, and taking a compass round the Square he scatteraEuro(TM)d Medals of Gold
